@node INTRO "Mimig V1.0 À Introduction"

 @{u}Introduction@{uu}

 Mimig is the first MUIRexx programm I wrote. I did it just for
 learning ARexx. As positive side effect I got a porgram that I wanted
 to have.

 Mimig is a GUI for MiamiNetStat. It is written in ARexx with the use
 of MUIRexx. It reloads MiamiNetStat by itself and shows the output in
 a nice MUI window.

 But do not afford too much. As written above, I am just learning how
 to use ARexx and MUIRexx. The style I use is not the best, I know. I
 do not know much about correct event handling and so I helped me with
 unefficient coding.
 So feel free to change the source to your needs. But let me know,
 what you did. I will release the best changes under a GNU public
 license way. I want to learn good coding.

 Send your changed scripts to the @{"Author" link AUTHOR}.

 @{u}Disclaimer@{uu}

 The author is not responsible for any damages the program Mimig causes.

@endnode
@node INSTALL "Mimig V1.0 À Installation"

 @{u}Installation@{uu}

 The installatin is easy. Just copy the provided script mimig.rexx to
 a place you want. Recommended is a own Rexxscript directory, where
 all scripts resides. This script should be in your path.

 You have to config the script to your own needs. The default settings
 are:

     PATH_MUIREXX   =  "sys:rexxc/MuiRexx"
     PATH_NETSTAT   =  "MIAMI:MiamiNetStat"
     WAIT_SECS      =  2

 @{FG shine}PATH_MUIREXX@{FG text} should be the path to the MUIRexx executable and
 @{FG shine}PATH_NETSTAT@{FG text} the path to MiamiNetStat. Do not forget to include the
 executable in this line. @{FG shine}WAIT_SECS@{FG text} tells the script how long the
 update periode should be.

 That should it be. Set the s bit to the script and you can start it
 with typing "mimig.rexx" in a shell window.

@endnode
@node USAGE "Mimig V1.0 À Usage"

 @{u}Usage@{uu}

 Yu can start the script after installation by typing @{FG shine}rx mimig@{FG text} or
 @{FG shine}rx mimig.rexx@{FG text} in shell window.

 There are only two objects in the window. A list where the output of
 MiamiNetStat will be displayed and a status bar which informs you
 about the status of Miami. Here can be displayed if its online,
 offline or not active.

@endnode
@node PROBLEMS "Mimig V1.0 À Known Problems"

 @{u}Known Problems@{uu}

 Developing this tool I found some bad bugs.

 o Menus are not stable. MUIRexx quits with a Guru when an About
   Requester was open and the list contents changed. So I removed
   menus.

 o If you close the window the script does not quit suddenly relating
   to what the script does in this moment.

 o Now errorhandling included.

 o ...

@endnode
@node FUTURE "Mimig V1.0 À Future"

 @{u}Future@{uu}

 The future depends on how I learn better coding. I have to know how
 to handle window closing better. The wait loop is too bad and not
 like I want.

 So feel free to contact me and give me some tips and improvements.
 Please read the @{"Introduction" link INTRO} and feel free to send me
 improved scripts.

 Nevertheless I plan:

 o Configwindow for Paths.

 o Updatetime selectable with a slider in the main window.

 o Improve the update loop.

 o The others wishes

@endnode
